      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle and cut the<strong> waxy potatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Tip: Cut some lengthways and some widthways for a more interesting texture!</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped waxy potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15-20 min or until tender, then drain and set aside to steam dry</p>",
